Description: Fragment of sub-round handle of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp with star symbols. Clay fine orange-brown.
Curator's comments: Name Aristokrates. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 80, 32? From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0077.11.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0611)
